x4freetext: The 13MV HI-13 Tandem Accelerator.
A metal hollow cylinder 9Be sample were used:
height=40 mm, inner diameter=10 mm, outer diameter=25
mm, weight=30.193 g.
Polyethylene: height=30 mm, inner diameter=10 mm,
outer diameter=30 mm, weight=17.02 g.
Deuterium gas target had following parameters:
30 x 10 mm in length and diameter, the thickness of
gold backing is 0.5 mm, the thickness of entrance Mo
foil is 10 um. The gas pressure is 0.6 MPa.
The measured raw TOF spectra are
included gas-in (sample-in/sample-out) and gas-
out (sample-in/sample-out). The net TOF spectra are
determined by gas-in/gas-out, and including the
propagation of uncertainties. The flight paths for 3
main detectors are 606.68, 657.88, 514.48 cm,
respectively. The flight path of monitor is 600.0 cm,
and set at 60 degree relative to the beam direction.
Three main detectors BC501A 180 x 100 mm in
diameter and height, with 200 keVee (electronic
energy) electron threshold, and one stilbene monitor
were used with 950 keVee.
For reduction of the experimental data, a detailed
Monte Carlo simulation was employed to obtain TOF
spectra, which were compared with the experimental
TOF spectra. The corrections due to the finite sample
size effects, flux attenuation and multiple scattering
, etc., were made with the Monte Carlo simulation.
To achieve the relative
measurement, the secondary neutron TOF spectra of
polyethylene were measured simultaneously, and the
elastic scattering of neutron by H (in the
polyethylene) has been used.)
The total uncertainty (~7%)
The counting statistical uncertainty (<2%)
The uncertainty of neutron detection
efficiency (~5%)
The uncertainty of the correction for
multiple scattering (~5%)
n-p monitor cross section (~1%)
Data were approved by author, 20140603.
Compiled by WANG Jimin (CNDC)
